radiographic_examinations.findings: Humeral head elevation with narrowing of the subacromial space as well as glenohumeral arthritis in the superior aspect of the joint.
Stress fracture in the lateral portion of the scapular spine and persisted high-riding humeral head.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: The stress fracture fully resolved after a two-month cessation of active shoulder motion.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Arthritic changes and the persistence of the high-riding humeral head.
